<TITLE> 'Militant' dies in Bagerhat shootout </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, Oct 1 (bdnews24.com)An alleged militant was killed in a 'gun battle' with the the joint force of RAB and police in Bagerhat early on Thursday amid the ongoing clampdown on extremist elements in the southwestern region. Reazul Haque Masud, 32, was a member of the banned Purbo Banglar Communist Party, police said. Bagerhat police superintendent Mohammed Mizanur Rahman said, acting on a tip-off, a police and RAB contingent had gone to raid a bamboo garden, a suspected militants' hangout in Chulkathhi under Khanpur union at around 3am. "The militants assembled there opened fire at the law enforcers and a gun battle ensued between the two parties. At one point, the militants withdrew and a bullet-hit Masud was found there," said the district police chief. After Masud was taken to Bagerhat sadar hospital, the doctors declared him dead, he added. Police said Masud faced 15 cases filed against him with different Bagerhat and Khulana police stations on charges of murders, extortion and other crimes. He was also involved in the murder of BNP leader M A Awal and Awami League leader S M Farhad Hossain, they said. The law-enforcement agencies have been active for about a month in the south and south-western districts to curb militancy. bdnews
